name: Frame Due Time
title: FDT
definition: Identifies the Frame Due Time assigned by the provider in response to special handling instructions for the connection, disconnection or coordination of changes for a request.

validEntry.description: Two Digit Hour (01-12)/Two Digit Minute (00-59)/AM or PM
Two Digit Hour (01-12)/A or P/Two Digit Hour (01-12)/A or P

validEntryNotes: Indicates the time zone and time or time zone and window of time when the service should be connected, disconnected or coordinated.
usageNotes: Required when the entry in this field is different than the FDT field on the ASR Form, otherwise optional.
